\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Sleep stages are categorized into two main types: Non-Rapid Eye Movement (NREM) sleep and Rapid Eye Movement (REM) sleep. These stages are characterized by distinct patterns of brain activity, eye movements, muscle tone, and physiological changes. Here's an overview of each stage:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Non-Rapid Eye Movement (NREM) Sleep
\f0\b0 :\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Stage N1
\f0\b0 : This is the transition stage between wakefulness and sleep. It's characterized by slow eye movements and relaxed muscle tone. Brain activity begins to slow down, and people can be easily awakened.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Stage N2
\f0\b0 : This is a deeper stage of sleep where eye movements stop, and brain waves become slower with occasional bursts of rapid activity known as sleep spindles. Muscle activity decreases further, and heart rate and body temperature drop.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl1
\f1\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Stage N3 (formerly Stage 3 and Stage 4)
\f0\b0 : This is the deepest stage of NREM sleep, also known as slow-wave sleep (SWS). It's characterized by slow, high-amplitude delta waves on EEG recordings. It's the most restorative stage of sleep, crucial for physical and mental recovery.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Rapid Eye Movement (REM) Sleep
\f0\b0 :\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 REM sleep is characterized by rapid eye movements, increased brain activity resembling wakefulness, and muscle paralysis (except for minor twitches). It's the stage associated with vivid dreams and memory consolidation.\cb1 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
